article.headline: Portland St. 81, Idaho St. 58
article.story: PORTLAND, Ore. (AP) -- Deonte Huff scored 20 points to lead Portland State to an 81-58 win over Idaho State on Thursday night. Jeremiah Dominguez added 18 points and five assists for the Vikings (16-8, 9-2 Big Sky Conference), who won their seventh straight game. Scott Morrison chipped in nine points for PSU. Austin Kilpatrick led Idaho State (9-15, 6-5) with 14 points and Matt Stucki scored 13 points for the Bengals. Portland State hit its first four shots, including three straight 3-pointers, to grab an 11-0 advantage in the opening minutes. The Vikings, who led the entire game, extended their lead to 28-9 when Kyle Coston connected on a 3-pointer with 9:07 remaining in the half. The Bengals cut the lead to 10 points early in the second half but a 24-4 run by PSU put the game out of reach. Portland State shot 46 percent and outrebounded the Bengals 41-25.
